newspaper trucks stopped rolling. News stands formerly piled
high with eight daily New York newspapers where
devoid of newspapers, devoid of customers.

11
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:54,773
Barron as a desert waste.

12
00:01:55,880 --> 00:02:01,743
With the lone exception of PM, news stands were as bare as
mother Hubbard's cupboard.

13
00:02:02,870 --> 00:02:08,780
13 million metropolitan new
Yorkers, deprived of their daily newspaper fair.

14
00:02:08,780 --> 00:02:13,670
And this at a time when
great events were in the making the world over.

15
00:02:13,670 --> 00:02:17,820
President Truman was on his way to a meeting of the big three.

16
00:02:17,820 --> 00:02:26,643
Japanese cities were
being laid waste by B-29s. Thousands of American boys were
returning home from European battlefields.

17
00:02:27,490 --> 00:02:33,080
Now newspapers were more than a habit, more than a convenience.

18
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:41,373
They were a necessity. Here then was the time
of all times for radio, the psychological moment.

19
00:02:42,290 --> 00:02:51,023
For years, the point has been argued, discussion has raised pro and
con, will radio eventually supplant newspaper?

20
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:55,843
Isn't it easier to turn a switch,
than to read an editorial?

21
00:02:57,130 --> 00:03:02,130
Yes, for radio, here was
a heaven sent opportunity.

22
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:08,290
Reluctant to profit by adversity. Hesitant to capitalize misfortune.

23
00:03:08,290 --> 00:03:14,340
Radio nevertheless had a job to do. A public service to perform.

24
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:22,270
And radio rose, nobly, to the occasion. Newscasters and commentators
labored long and hard.

25
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:31,840
Radio news programs were
substantially increased. Many newspapers either started
or increased their regular news radio roundup.

26
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:38,500
The times was on the air
every hour, on the hour. The Herald Tribune had
a regular news period.

27
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:43,160
The news doubled its schedule. Went on the air 48 times a day.

28
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:50,050
At almost any hour, day or night. The public could flip a
dial, and hear a newscast.

29
00:03:50,050 --> 00:03:56,860
Certainly if news by a radio, could satisfy the news hungry public.

30
00:03:56,860 --> 00:03:59,573
Radio was giving it every chance.

31
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:06,977
But something was lacking, an appetizer is a poor
substitute for a full meal.

32
