On the last day of the strike, the Herald Tribune sold 65,000 copies.

40
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:17,750
By far, the greater
portion of them in direct, over the counter sale, to Tribune readers, who had taken the time and
trouble, to come far out of their way to get a copy
of their favorite morning newspaper.

41
